Enable PCIe bus 1 + modem PHY for the SDX55 5G modem

The Xiaomi POCO F2 Pro (xiaomi-lmi) uses an external Qualcomm SDX55
modem connected over PCIe bus 1 (pcie@1c08000) with a dedicated
modem PCIe PHY (pcie1_phy). Both nodes are 'disabled' in sm8250.dtsi.

Enabling them lets the generic MHI PCI driver (mhi_pci_generic)
auto-probe the modem via its PCI ID 17cb:0306. The modem then exposes
QMI/QRTR interfaces usable by ModemManager.

Requires the modem firmware blobs qcom/sdx55m/sbl1.mbn and edl.mbn.

Signed-off-by: macosmojave2 <macosmojave2@gmail.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8250-xiaomi-lmi.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8250-xiaomi-lmi.dts
@@ -869,6 +869,23 @@
 	};
 };
 
+/*
+ * PCIe bus 1 connects the external SDX55 5G modem (Snapdragon X55).
+ * The modem itself is auto-probed by the mhi_pci_generic driver via its
+ * PCI ID (17cb:0306), so only the host bridge + modem PHY need enabling here.
+ */
+&pcie1 {
+	vdda-supply = <&vreg_l9a_1p2>;
+	vddpe-3v3-supply = <&vreg_l11c_3p3>;
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&pcie1_phy {
+	vdda-phy-supply = <&vreg_s6c_0p88>;
+	vdda-pll-supply = <&vreg_l9a_1p2>;
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
 &pcie2 {
 	vdda-supply = <&vreg_l9a_1p2>;
 	vddpe-3v3-supply = <&vreg_l11c_3p3>;
